This paper deals with the analysis of consistency in distributed key-value stores, which is a topic that falls under the categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Databases (cs.DB). The paper also uses probabilistic models to analyze the consistency guarantees, which could fall under the categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Probability (cs.PF).
